midity. However, by reducing surface evaporation, the new soil hydraulic parameters cause the model to become warmer during the summer. The new two-stream multi-layer canopy radiation scheme is found to cool the model by about 0·25 K during the summer. In our trials, the effect of the full changes is to eliminate the UM NH summer warm bias.},
